Dr. Governor Okezie Ikpeazu has delivered visible and qualitative achievements for Abia State since his election as Governor of the state. A progress report released on Saturday, outlined some achievements under his leadership. The Governor has completed different roads, water and school projects, while ensuring that it gets optimal value for every money he spent. The Ikpeazu-led administration has also embarked on massive road projects across the state. Some of the completed projects include, Back2Back , Abia State school feed program, Abia State poultry cluster project, four new rice mills in Uzuakoli, large scale mushroom production, SME development, e.t.c The administration has also made concerted efforts in attracting investments to the state. Such example is the multi-Skill and Entrepreneur Centre in Umuobiakwa. Ikpeazu has equally shown commitment towards providing water to the different local government areas and has maintained a cordial working relationship with the legislative arm which has led to most of the successes recorded so far. See pictures below <img class="aligncenter wp-image-823499 size-full" src="https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/Capture-1.png" alt="" width="801" height="568" srcset="https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/Capture-1.png 801w, https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/Capture-1-300x213.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 801px) 100vw, 801px"> <img class="aligncenter wp-image-823500 size-full" src="https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/Capture-2.png" alt="" width="802" height="538" srcset="https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/Capture-2.png 802w, https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/Capture-2-300x201.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 802px) 100vw, 802px">